subSubSection.paragraph:
Description
. Forewing without coloration. Venation distinct with apparent intercalaries and rich cross-veins in M and CuA. Subcostal area wide, with Sc richly branched (secondarily). R regular, parallel; M (
5
) slightly curved, running close to R (apomorphy), fusing to CuA. CuA rich (
8
). Anal veins simple with punctuated intercalaries.
